paragraphs.text: %md Run the paragraph below to download and extract the [Maxmind GeoLiteCity database](http://dev.maxmind.com/geoip/legacy/geolite/).

result.msg: Run the paragraph below to download and extract the Maxmind GeoLiteCity database.

paragraphs.text:
%sh

cd /var/lib/data/geo
if [ ! -f GeoLiteCity.dat ]; then
    curl -s -O http://geolite.maxmind.com/download/geoip/database/GeoLiteCity.dat.gz
    gzip -d GeoLiteCity.dat.gz
fi

%md

Add a third-party **Repository** for [maven.snplow.com](http://maven.snplow.com/releases) in Zeppelin's Interpreter configuration. *Hint: It's the gear icon in the upper-right.*

- `id`: snowplow
- `url`: http://maven.snplow.com/releases
- `snapshot`: false

Edit the **Spark** Interpreter and add `com.snowplowanalytics:scala-maxmind-iplookups_2.11:0.2.0` as a dependency. artifact. Once complete, the following paragraph should run successfully.

  • id: snowplow
  • url: http://maven.snplow.com/releases

Edit the Spark Interpreter and add com.snowplowanalytics:scala-maxmind-iplookups_2.11:0.2.0 as a dependency. artifact. Once complete, the following paragraph should run successfully.

paragraphs.text:
%spark

import com.snowplowanalytics.maxmind.iplookups.IpLookups

val ipLookups = IpLookups(geoFile = Some("/var/lib/data/geo/GeoLiteCity.dat"))

for (location <- ipLookups.performLookupsWithoutLruCache("98.237.177.9")._1) {
  println(location.countryCode)     // "US"
  println(location.countryName)     // "United States" 
  println(location.city.get)        // "Bellevue" 
  println(location.regionName.get)  // "Washington" 
  println(location.latitude)        // "47.620102" 
  println(location.longitude)       // "-122.1408" 
}
